Estimations (Part A)

The general model for estimation is as follows:

\[\begin{align*} \text{ln } p_{ijk} &= \alpha + \beta sim_{ij} + \gamma_1 \rho_k + \gamma_2 \theta_{ij} + \gamma_3 tariff_{ijk} \\ & + \gamma_4 NTM_{ijk}^{Tech} + \gamma_5 NTM_{ijk}^{Non-Tech} + \gamma_{6i}(NTM_{ijk}^{Tech} \times \delta_i) + \gamma_{7i}(NTM_{ijk}^{Non-Tech} \times \delta_i) \\ & + \gamma_8 DIG_i + \epsilon_{ijk} \end{align*}\]

where

\(DIG_i\) is the average score of separate Pillar measures capturing digital-trade regulation imposed by country \(i\) on all imports
\(\rho\) is the HS6 product fixed effects dummy variable (since regressions are estimated at chapter-level (i.e. there are 96 separate regressions)
\(\theta\) is the pair characteristics (i.e. distance, contiguity, landlocked status, common language, and RTA)
\(tariff_{ijk}\) is the applied tariff (MFN or lowest preferential, if available) imposed by \(i\) on imports of product \(k\) from \(j\)
\(NTM_{ijk}^{Tech}\) is the count of separate non-tariff measures from chapters A to C imposed by \(i\) on imports of product \(k\) from \(j\)
\(NTM_{ijk}^{Non-Tech}\) is the count of separate non-tariff measures from chapters D to O imposed by \(i\) on imports of product \(k\) from \(j\)
\(sim_{ij}\) is a measure of regulatory similarity of country \(i\) and \(j\)
\(\delta_{i}\) is fixed effect of country \(i\) (included for interaction with \(NTM\))

Model 1

\[\begin{align*} \text{ln } p_{ijk} &= \alpha + \beta sim_{ij} + \epsilon_{ijk} \end{align*}\]

library(dplyr)

reporter.aves <- aves.dta %>%
  group_by(reporteriso3) %>% 
  summarise(ave_weighted = weighted.mean(NNeg, tradevalue, na.rm = TRUE))
# summarise(ave_mean = mean(aves.dta$POS, na.rm = TRUE))

reporter.aves$names <- c("Australia", "Brunei", "China", "Hong Kong", "India", "Indonesia", "Japan", "Cambodia",
   "Korea, Rep.", "Kazakhstan", "Lao", "Malaysia", "Nepal", "New Zealand", "Pakistan",
   "Phillipines", "Russia", "Singapore", "Thailand", "Turkey", "Vietnam", "Vanuatu")
reporter.aves$grp <- c(3, 3, 2, 3, 2, 2, 3, 1, 3, 2, 1, 2, 1, 3, 1, 2, 2, 3, 2, 3, 1, 1)
library(ggplot2)

reporter.aves<-reporter.aves[!(reporter.aves$ave_weighted=="NaN"),]

ggplot(data = reporter.aves, aes(x = grp, y = ave_weighted, fill = reporteriso3)) +
    geom_bar(stat="identity", position ="dodge") +
